Package: mmirestriktor
Title: Informative Hypothesis Testing Web Applications
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Mackson", "Ncube", , "macksonncube.stats@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("mightymetrika, LLC", role = c("cph", "fnd"))
  )
Description: Offering enhanced statistical power compared to traditional methods,
    informative hypothesis testing allows researchers to explicitly model their
    expectations regarding the relationships among parameters. An important
    software tool for this framework is 'restriktor'. The 'mmirestriktor' package
    provides 'shiny' web applications to implement some basic functionality of
    'restriktor'; moreover, 'mmirestriktor' includes development tools for
    building custom 'shiny' applications using 'restriktor'. The mmirestriktor()
    function launches a 'shiny' application for fitting and analyzing models with
    constraints. The FbarCards() function launches a card game application to
    build intuition about informative hypothesis testing. The iht_interpreter()
    helps interpret informative hypothesis testing results based on guidelines
    in Vanbrabant and Rosseel (2020) <doi:10.4324/9780429273872-14>. Overall,
    'mmirestriktor' facilitates leveraging the capabilities of 'restriktor' for
    informative hypothesis testing via interactive web applications.
